  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Kaushal Singh versus The State of Rajasthan pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_7_1221_1232','2025INSC871'); ><font size='4'> <strong>KAUSHAL SINGH<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF RAJASTHAN </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 1221</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 871</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007912025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANJAY KAROL, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Matter pertains to the expunction of strictures passed by the High Court against the Judicial Officer. Headnotes&dagger; Strictures &ndash; Strictures against the judicial officers &ndash; Expunction &ndash; High Court passed strictures against the Judicial Officer that granting bail to the accused in a grossly inappropriate and cavalier manner while ignoring the criminal record of the accused; and that the act of the Judicial Officer tantamounted to indiscipline, negligence and, ignorance and disobedience of the orders passed by the High Court, and directed<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 18-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 3053/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_7_1221_1232','2025INSC871','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-